cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper is about evaluating the ability of models to reason with quantities in textual entailment, which is a task related to natural language understanding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a new baseline model for quantitative reasoning, which involves symbolic manipulation of quantities, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of existing models, which suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
